obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (46331)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title. Extent of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46331&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called "The Bombay Civil Courts' Act, 1869," and`
  line `extends only to the territories (other than Sind) under the Government of the Governor of Bombay in`
  line `Council in which the Code of Civil Procedure is now in force. But the Governor of Bombay in Council`
  line `may, by notification in the Government Gazette, extend this Act to any other of the territories under such`
  line `Government in which the said Code is not in force, or to Sind.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (46332)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46332&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `[Repeal of enactments].--Rep. by the Obsolete Enactments Act, 1870 (14 of 1870), s. 1 and`
  line `Schedule, Part II (w.e.f. 5-4-1870).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (46333)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Alteration and creation of Districts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46333&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Governor of Bombay in Council may from time to`
  line `time, by notification in the Government Gazette, alter the limits of existing Zilas (which. shall hereafter`
  line `be called Districts) and create new Districts for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (46334)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Position of Sadr station.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46334&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Governor of Bombay in Council may also from time to time, by`
  line `notification in the Government Gazette, alter the position of the Sadar station in any District, and fix the`
  line `position of the Sadr station in any new District.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (46335)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `District Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. The second paragraph of section 5 rep. by Act 12 of 1876, s. 1 and Schedule, Part I (w.e.f. 11-4-1876).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46335&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `There shall be in each District a District Court presided over by a Judge to be`
  line `called the District Judge. He shall be appointed by the Governor of Bombay in Council by whose`
  line `authority only he shall be liable to be suspended or removed from his appointment.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (46336)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Situation of District Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46336&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The District Judge shall ordinarily hold the District Court at the`
  line `Sadr station in his District, but may, with the previous sanction of the High Court, hold it elsewhere`
  line `within the District.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (46337)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Original jurisdiction of District Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46337&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The District Court shall be the principal Court of`
  line `original civil jurisdiction in the District, within the meaning of the Code of Civil Procedure.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (46338)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `His appellate jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46338&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Except as provided in sections sixteen, seventeen and twenty-six, the`
  line `District Court shall be the Court of Appeal from all decrees and orders passed by the Subordinate Courts`
  line `from which an appeal lies under any law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (46339)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Control and inspection of Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46339&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The District Judge shall have general control over all the`
  line `Civil Courts and their establishments within the District, and it shall be his duty to inspect, or to cause one`
  line `of his Assistants to inspect, the proceedings of all the Courts subordinate to him, and to give such`
  line `directions with respect to matters not provided for by law as he may think necessary. The District Judge`
  line `shall also refer to the High Court all such matters as appear to him to require that a rule of that Court`
  line `should be made thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (46340)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Writs and orders. Reports and returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46340&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The District Judge shall obey all writs, orders, or`
  line `processes issued to him by the High Court, and shall make such returns or reports thereto under his`
  line `signature and the seal of the Court as the exigencies of the case require. He shall further furnish such`
  line `reports and returns and copies of proceedings as may be called for by the High Court or the Governor of`
  line `Bombay in Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (46341)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Seal of District Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46341&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The District Judge shall use a circular seal two inches in diameter,`
  line `which shall bear thereon the. Royal Arms with the following inscription in English and the principal`
  line `language of the District—“District Court of .”`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (46342)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to appoint Joint Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46342&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Governor of Bombay in Council may, with the previous`
  line `sanction of the Governor General of India in Council, appoint in any District a Joint Judge who shall be`
  line `invested with co-extensive powers and a concurrent jurisdiction with the District Judge, except that he`
  line `shall not keep a file of civil suits and shall transact such civil business only as he may receive from the`
  line `District Judge, or as may have been referred to the Joint Judge by order of the High Court.`
  line
  line `When the appointment of a Joint Judge shall have been sanctioned by the Governor General of India`
  line `in Council, the Governor of Bombay in Council may, so long as such sanction continues in force, appoint`
  line `a successor to such Joint Judge in case his office becomes vacant, or transfer such Joint Judge from one`
  line `District to another; and in such other District the Joint Judge so transferred shall have the same powers as`
  line `he had in the former District.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (46343)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Enactments applying to District Judge to apply to Joint Judge. Joint Judge’s seal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46343&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line All
  line `Regulations and Acts now or hereafter in force and applying to a District Judge shall be deemed to apply`
  line `also to the Joint Judge; and the seal of the Joint Judge shall be the same as is used by the District Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (46344)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to appoint Assistant Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. The second paragraph of section 14 rep. by Act 12 of 1876, s. 1 and Schedule, Part I (w.e.f. 11-4-1876).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46344&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Governor of Bombay in Council, under the general`
  line `control of the Governor General of India in Council, may appoint one or more Assistants to the District`
  line `Judge, and may suspend or remove from his appointment any Assistant so appointed.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (46345)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Situation of Assistant Judge’s Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46345&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `An Assistant Judge shall ordinarily hold his Court at the`
  line `same place as the District Judge, but he may hold his Court elsewhere within the District, whenever the`
  line `District Judge shall, with the previous sanction of the High Court, direct him so to do.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (46346)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Original jurisdiction of Assistant Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Certain words repealed by Act 7 of 1889, s. 2 and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 8-3-1889).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46346&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The District Judge may refer to any Assistant Judge`
  line `subordinate to him original suits of which the subject-matter does not amount to ten thousand rupees in`
  line `amount or value, and miscellaneous applications not being of the nature of appeals. The Assistant Judge`
  line `shall have jurisdiction to try such suits and to dispose of such applications. Where the Assistant Judge's`
  line `decrees and orders in such cases are appealable, the appeal shall lie to the District Judge or to the High`
  line `Court according as the amount or value of the subject-matter does not exceed or exceeds five thousand`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `The Assistant Judge shall, when directed by the District Judge so to do, also take evidence on`
  line `applications for certificates under ^1`
  line `*** Act No. 20 of 1864 (for making better provision for the care of the`
  line `persons and property of minors in, the Presidency of Bombay), and shall forward it with his opinion`
  line `thereon for the final orders of the District Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (46347)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Appellate jurisdiction of Assistant Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46347&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Governor of Bombay in Council may, by`
  line `notification in the Government Gazette, empower any Assistant Judge to try such appeals from the`
  line `decrees and orders of the subordinate Courts as would lie to the District Judge and as may be referred by`
  line `him to the Assistant Judge.`
  line
  line `Decrees and orders passed under this section by an Assistant Judge shall have the same force and`
  line `shall be subject to the same rules as regards procedure and appeals as decrees and orders passed by the`
  line `District Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (46348)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Continuance of Assistant Judge’s appellate jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46348&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `A person filling the office of`
  line `Assistant Judge, on whom the power of hearing appeals has once been conferred under section seventeen,`
  line `shall continue to have this power so long and so often as he may fill the office, of Assistant Judge,`
  line `without reference to the District in which he may be employed; provided that the Governor of Bombay in`
  line `Council may, by notification in the Government Gazette, at any time withdraw such power.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (46349)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to invest Assistant Judge with powers of District Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46349&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Governor of Bombay in`
  line `Council may, by notification in the Government Gazette, invest an Assistant Judge with all or any of the`
  line `powers of a District Judge within a particular part of a District, and may, by like notification, from time to`
  line `time determine and alter the limits of such Part.`
  line
  line `The jurisdiction of an Assistant Judge so invested shall pro tanto exclude the jurisdiction of the`
  line `District Judge from within the said limits.`
  line
  line `Every Assistant Judge so invested shall ordinarily hold his Court at such place within the local limits`
  line `of his jurisdiction as may be determined by the Governor of Bombay in Council, and may, with the`
  line `previous sanction of the High Court, hold it at any other place within such limits.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (46350)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Assistant Judge to use seal of District Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46350&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Every Assistant Judge shall use the seal of the`
  line `District Judge to whom he is Assistant.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (46351)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Number of Subordinate Civil Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46351&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `There shall be in each District so many Civil Courts`
  line `subordinate to the District Court as the Governor of Bombay in Council, acting under the general control`
  line `of the Governor General of India in Council, shall from time to time direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (46352)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Appointment of Subordinate Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46352&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The Judges of such subordinate Courts shall be`
  line `appointed by the Governor of Bombay in Council, and shall be called Subordinate Judges.`
  line
  line `No person shall be appointed a Subordinate Judge unless he be a subject of the Queen who has`
  line `practised five years as an Advocate of a High Court in India or as a Vakil in the High Court of Judicature`
  line `in Bombay, or who has qualified for the duties of a Subordinate Judge according to such tests as may for`
  line `the time being be prescribed by such High Court, or who has taken the degree of Bachelor of Laws in the`
  line `University of Bombay.`
  line
  line `The tests so prescribed by the High Court shall be notified in the Government Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22_a:
  sectionId (46353)
  sectionNo 22A
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to fix local Jurisdiction of Subordinate Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1880, s. 2 (w.e.f. 30-4-1880).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46353&sectionno=22A&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[22A. Power to fix local limits of jurisdiction of Subordinate Judges.The Governor of Bombay`
  line `in Council may, by notification in the official Gazette, fix, and, by a like notification, from time to time`
  line `alter, the local limits of the ordinary jurisdiction of the Subordinate Judges.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (46354)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Situation of Subordinate Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46354&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Subordinate Judges shall hold their Courts at such place`
  line `or places as the Governor of Bombay in Council may from time to time appoint, within the local limits of`
  line `their respective jurisdictions. Wherever more than one such place is appointed, the District Judge shall,`
  line `subject to the control of the High Court, fix the days on which the Subordinate Judge shall hold his Court`
  line `at each of such places, and the Subordinate Judge shall cause such days to be duly notified throughout the`
  line `local limits of his jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `The same person may be the Judge of more than one Subordinate Court; and in such cases the District`
  line `judge shall, subject to the control of the High Court, prescribe rules for regulating the time during which`
  line `the Subordinate Judge shall sit in each Court.`
  line
  line `The Judge of any Subordinate Court may, with the previous sanction of the High Court, be deputed`
  line `by the District Judge to the Court of another Subordinate Judge for the purpose of assisting him in the`
  line `disposal of the suits on his file.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (46355)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Classes of Subordinate Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46355&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Subordinate Judges shall be of two classes.`
  line
  line `Jurisdiction of Subordinate Judge of first class.—The jurisdiction of a Subordinate Judge of the`
  line `first class extends to all original suits and proceedings of a civil nature.`
  line
  line `Jurisdiction of Subordinate Judges of second class.—The jurisdiction of a Subordinate Judge of`
  line `the second class extends to all original suits and proceedings of a civil nature wherein the subject-matter`
  line `does not exceed in amount or value five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (46356)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Special jurisdiction of Subordinate Judge of first class.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46356&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `A Subordinate Judge of the first`
  line `class, in addition to his ordinary jurisdiction, shall exercise a special jurisdiction in respect of such suits`
  line `and proceedings of a civil nature wherein the subject-matter exceeds five thousand rupees in amount or`
  line `value as may arise within the local jurisdictions of the Courts in the District presided over by Subordinate`
  line `Judges of the second class.`
  line
  line `In Districts to which more than one Subordinate Judge of the first class have been appointed, the`
  line `District Judge, subject to the orders of the High Court, shall assign to each the local limits within which`
  line `his said special jurisdiction is to be exercised.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (46357)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Appeals from his decision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46357&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `In all suits decided by a Subordinate Judge ^1`
  line `*** of which the`
  line `amount or value of the subject-matter exceeds five thousand rupees, the appeal from his decision shall be`
  line `direct to the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "of the first class in the exercise of his ordinary and special original jurisdiction" omitted by Act 28 of 1930,`
  line `s. 2 (w.e.f. 25-7-1930).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (46358)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Appellate jurisdiction of Subordinate Judge of first class.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46358&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The Governor of Bombay in`
  line `Council may invest any Subordinate Judge of the first class with power to hear appeals from such decrees`
  line `and orders of Subordinate Courts as may be referred to him by the Judge of the District.`
  line
  line `Decrees and orders so passed in appeal by a Subordinate Judge of the first class shall have the same,`
  line `force as if passed by a District Judge.`
  line
  line `The Governor of Bombay in Council may, whenever he thinks fit, withdraw such jurisdiction from`
  line `any Subordinate Judge so invested.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (46359)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to invest Subordinate Judges with small cause powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46359&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The Governor of Bombay in`
  line `Council may invest, within such local limits as he shall from time to time appoint, any Subordinate Judge`
  line `of the first class with the jurisdiction of a Judge of a Court of Small Causes, for the trial of suits`
  line `cognizable by such Courts up to the amount of five hundred rupees, and any Subordinate Judge of the`
  line `second class with the same jurisdiction up to the amount of fifty rupees.`
  line
  line `The Governor of Bombay in Council may, whenever he thinks fit, withdraw such jurisdiction from`
  line `any Subordinate Judge so invested.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (46360)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Seal of Subordinate Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46360&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Each Subordinate Judge shall use a seal one inch and a half in`
  line `diameter, bearing the Royal Crown with the following inscription in English and the principal language of`
  line `the District—“Subordinate Judge of .”`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (46361)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46361&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `[First Subordinate Judges of first class].—Rep. by the Obsolete Enactments Act, 1876 (12 of`
  line `1876), s. 1 and Schedule, Part I (w.e.f. 11-4-1876).`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (46362)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Pending proceedings].—Rep. by s. 1 and Schedule, Part I, ibid. (w.e.f. 11-4-1876).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46362&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (46363)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Reference of Government suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46363&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `^1[No Subordinate Judge or Court of Small Causes shall`
  line `receive or register a suit in which the Government or any officer of Government in his official capacity is`
  line `a party, but in every such case such Judge or Court shall refer the plaintiff to the District Judge, in whose`
  line `Court alone (subject to the provisions of section nineteen) such suit shall be instituted.]`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to apply to any suit merely because—`
  line
  line `(a) a municipal corporation constituted under Bombay Act No. 6 of 1873, or any other enactment`
  line `for the time being in force, is a party to such suit and an officer of Government is in his official`
  line `capacity a member of such corporation, or`
  line
  line `(b) an officer of a Court appointed under the Code of Civil Procedure, section 456, last paragraph,`
  line ^3
  line `*** a party to such suit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 1876, s. 15, for certain words (w.e.f. 28-3-1876).`
  line
  line `2. Added by Act 15 of 1880, s. 3 (w.e.f. 3-11-1880).`
  line
  line `3. Certain words rep. by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and the First Schedule, Part I (w.e.f. 21-3-1891).`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (46364)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 34
  title `Commission of enquiry into alleged misconduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46364&sectionno=33&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the High Court is of opinion that`
  line `there are good grounds for making a formal and public enquiry into the truth of any imputation of`
  line `misconduct by any Subordinate Judge, the High Court may appoint a Commissioner or Commissioners`
  line `for the purpose of holding such an enquiry, and on the receipt of his or their report may order that the`
  line `Subordinate Judge be removed or suspended from office, or reduced to a lower class.`
  line
  line `The provisions of Act No. 37 of 1850 (for regulating enquiries into the behaviour of public servants)`
  line `shall apply to enquiries under this section, the powers conferred by that Act on the Government being`
  line `exercised by the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (46365)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 35
  title `Suspension of Subordinate Judges by High Court or District Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46365&sectionno=34&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may`
  line `suspend any Subordinate Judge from office pending the result of an enquiry into his behaviour under this`
  line section.
  line
  line `Any District Judge may, whenever he sees urgent necessity for so doing, suspend from office any`
  line `Subordinate Judge under his control. But whenever the District Judge suspends any such Subordinate`
  line `Judge, he shall forthwith report the case for the orders of the High Court.`
  line
  line `Saving of power of Government to suspend or dismiss.—Nothing in this section or in section`
  line `thirty-three shall be held to interfere with the right of Government to suspend, or remove from office, any`
  line `Subordinate Judge at their discretion.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (46366)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 36
  title `Temporary vacancy of office of District Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46366&sectionno=35&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `In the event of the death of the District Judge`
  line `or of his being prevented from performing his duties by illness or other casualty, or of his absence from`
  line `his District on leave, the first in rank of the Assistant Judges in the District, or in the absence from the`
  line `District of an Assistant Judge the first in rank of the Subordinate Judges, shall assume charge of the`
  line `District Court without interruption to his ordinary jurisdiction,. and while so in charge shall perform the`
  line `duties of a District judge with respect to the filing of suits and appeals, receiving pleadings, execution of`
  line `processes, return of writs and the like, and shall be designated Assistant Judge or Subordinate Judge, as`
  line `the case May be, in charge of the District, and shall continue in such charge until the office of District`
  line `Judge may be resumed or assumed by an officer duly appointed thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (46367)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 37
  title `Delegation of powers of District Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46367&sectionno=36&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Any District Judge leaving the Sadr station and`
  line `proceeding on duty to any place within his District, may delegate to an Assistant Judge, or in the absence`
  line `of an Assistant Judge to a Subordinate Judge at the Sadr station, the power of performing such of the`
  line `duties enumerated in section thirty-five as may be emergent; and such officer shall be designated`
  line `Assistant or Subordinate Judge, as the case may be, in charge of the Sadr station.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (46368)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 38
  title `Temporary vacancy of office of Subordinate Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46368&sectionno=37&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `In the event of the death, suspension or`
  line `temporary absence of any Subordinate Judge, the District Judge may empower the Judge of any`
  line `Subordinate Court of the same District to perform the duties of the Judge of the vacated Subordinate`
  line `Court, either at the place of such Court or of his own Court; but in every such case the Registers and`
  line `Records of the two Courts shall be kept distinct.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (46369)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 39
  title `Appointment, &c., of ministerial officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46369&sectionno=38&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `All ministerial officers of the Civil Courts in each`
  line `District shall be appointed, and may be fined, suspended or dismissed by the District Judge, subject to`
  line `such rules as the High Court may from time to time prescribe:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Judge of every Subordinate Court may, subject to the like rules, appoint the`
  line `ministerial officers of such Court, whose salaries do not exceed rupees ten per mensem, and may by order`
  line `find, suspend or dismiss any ministerial officer of such Court who is guilty of any misconduct or neglect`
  line `in the performance of the duties of his office. Every such order shall be subject to appeal to the District`
  line `Judge; and the roles for the time being applicable to appeals to the Court of Session from orders of the`
  line `Criminal Courts subordinate thereto, shall apply to all appeals under this section.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section shall exempt the offender from any penal or other consequences to which he`
  line `may be liable under any other law in force for the time being.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (46370)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 40
  title `Duties of ministerial officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46370&sectionno=39&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The duties of the said ministerial officers shall be regulated by`
  line `such rules as the High Court may from time to time prescribe.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (46371)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power to appoint Clerks of the Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46371&sectionno=40&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The Governor of Bombay in Council may, under the`
  line `general control of the Governor General of India in Council, appoint to any. Civil Court under this Act a`
  line `Clerk of the Court who, in addition to such duties as may from time to time be prescribed by the High`
  line `Court, may receive and register plaints, and shall refer such as he may consider should be refused for the`
  line `orders of the Judge of the Court, and may sign all processes, and authenticate copies of papers.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (46372)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 42
  title `Rules for keeping proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46372&sectionno=41&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `The proceedings of each Civil Court shall be kept and`
  line `recorded according to such rules as the High Court may from time to time prescribe. The High Court shall`
  line `also lay down rules under which copies of papers may be granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (46373)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 43
  title `Fees for process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46373&sectionno=42&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The High Court shall from time to time, with the sanction of the Governor of`
  line `Bombay in Council, prescribe and regulate the fees to be taken for any process issued by any Court the`
  line `constitution of which is declared by this Act, or by any officer of such Court.`
  line
  line `Tables of the fees so prescribed shall be published in the Government Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (46374)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 44
  title `Sittings of Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336&sectionId=46374&sectionno=43&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00022_186914_1523268305336
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The District and Subordinate Courts shall sit from day to day, except on`
  line `Sundays, New Year's Day, Good Friday, Christmas Day, and Her Majesty's Birth Day, and such other`
  line `days as may be sanctioned for each or every District by the High Court.`
  line
  line `Vacation.—The High Court may also permit the Civil Courts under its control to adjourn for a period`
  line `or periods not exceeding in the whole six weeks in each year.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
